name: Column
description: Describes a column on a DataSource.Table. This class extends the DataSourceUtil class and inherits its methods.

decimalplaces.name: decimalPlaces
decimalplaces.description: If the data type is numeric, the number of decimal places to the right of the decimal point.

description.name: description
description.description: Description of what the column represents.

filterable.name: filterable
filterable.description: Whether a result set can be filtered based on the values of the column.

label.name: label
label.description: User-friendly name for the column that appears in the Salesforce user interface.

length.name: length
length.description: If the column is a string data type, the number of characters in the column. If the column is a numeric data type, the total number of digits on both sides of the decimal point, but excluding the decimal point.

name.name: name
name.description: Name of the column in the external system.

referencetargetfield.name: referenceTargetField
referencetargetfield.description: API name of the custom field on the parent object whose values are compared against this column’s values. Matching values identify related records in an indirect lookup relationship. Applies only when the column’s data type is INDIRECT_LOOKUP_TYPE. For other data types, this value is ignored.

referenceto.name: referenceTo
referenceto.description: API name of the parent object in the relationship that’s represented by this column. Applies only when the column’s data type is LOOKUP_TYPE, EXTERNAL_LOOKUP_TYPE, or INDIRECT_LOOKUP_TYPE. For other data types, this value is ignored.

sortable.name: sortable
sortable.description: Whether a result set can be sorted based on the values of the column via an ORDER BY clause.

boolean(string).name: boolean
boolean(string).description: Returns a new column of data type BOOLEAN_TYPE.

externallookup(string,string).name: externalLookup
externallookup(string,string).signature: public static DataSource.Column externalLookup(String name, String domain)
externallookup(string,string).description: Returns a new column of data type EXTERNAL_LOOKUP_TYPE.

get(string,string,string,boolean,boolean.name: get
get(string,string,string,boolean,boolean.signature: public static DataSource.Column get(String name, String label, String description, Boolean isSortable, Boolean isFilterable, DataSource.DataType type, Integer length, Integer decimalPlaces, String referenceTo, String referenceTargetField)
get(string,string,string,boolean,boolean.description: Returns a new column with the ten specified Column property values.

get(string,string,string,boolean,boolean.description: Returns a new column with the eight specified Column property values.

get(string,string,string,boolean,boolean.signature: public static DataSource.Column get(String name, String label, String description, Boolean isSortable, Boolean isFilterable, DataSource.DataType type, Integer length)
get(string,string,string,boolean,boolean.description: Returns a new column with the seven specified Column property values.

indirectlookup(string,string,string).signature: public static DataSource.Column indirectLookup(String name, String domain, String targetField)
indirectlookup(string,string,string).description: Returns a new column of data type INDIRECT_LOOKUP_TYPE.

integer(string,integer).signature: public static DataSource.Column integer(String name, Integer length)
integer(string,integer).description: Returns a new numeric column with no decimal places using the specified name and length.

lookup(string,string).signature: public static DataSource.Column lookup(String name, String domain)
lookup(string,string).description: Returns a new column of data type LOOKUP_TYPE.

number(string,integer,integer).description: Returns a new column of data type NUMBER_TYPE.

text(string,string,integer).description: Returns a new column of data type STRING_SHORT_TYPE or STRING_LONG_TYPE, with the specified name, label, and length.

text(string,integer).signature: public static DataSource.Column text(String name, Integer length)
text(string,integer).description: Returns a new column of data type STRING_SHORT_TYPE or STRING_LONG_TYPE, with the specified name and length.

text(string).name: text
text(string).description: Returns a new column of data type STRING_SHORT_TYPE with the specified name and the length of 255 characters.

textarea(string).name: textarea
textarea(string).description: Returns a new column of data type STRING_LONG_TYPE with the specified name and the length of 32,000 characters.

url(string,integer).description: Returns a new column of data type URL_TYPE with the specified name and length.

url(string).name: url
url(string).description: Returns a new column of data type URL_TYPE with the specified name and the length of 1,000 characters.
